TuxRadio is a miniature linux system with a CSM radio interface.

FLASHING FIRMWARE

To update CSMs firmware with culfw execute:

	make program

on the TuxRadio itself. This will require some tools installed upfront. 
Use:

	apt-get install make avrdude


to flash the recompiled CSM.hex file.

USING

The culfw stack is available on: /dev/ttySP1@38400
